WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:25.000
Zettalogix v0.3 begins in a visibly bounded synthetic workspace. Fictional local state is separated from external migration, identity, and provider services.

00:25.000 --> 00:50.000
Cross-workspace search resolves jobs, connections, and help topics from the current in-memory dataset.

00:50.000 --> 01:15.000
The migration ledger shows running and completed synthetic work without claiming a connected worker.

01:15.000 --> 01:40.000
The four-step blueprint covers discovery, source, destination, and review while preserving the external-backend boundary.

01:40.000 --> 02:10.000
A legal-records draft is created in local state with inspectable source, destination, and metadata fields.

02:10.000 --> 02:40.000
Starting the draft adds deterministic progress and event evidence without a network request.

02:40.000 --> 03:10.000
Pausing the job records another local operator event. Reset restores the repeatable baseline.

03:10.000 --> 03:35.000
Readiness is derived only from connection health, mapping fields, failure count, and event history. It is not predictive AI.

03:35.000 --> 04:00.000
The connection inventory uses fictional values and does not load provider SDKs in demo mode.

04:00.000 --> 04:25.000
A synthetic connection check updates local state and produces visible confirmation.

04:25.000 --> 04:50.000
Concurrency, retries, notifications, and telemetry are browser-only planning defaults here.

04:50.000 --> 05:15.000
The help center documents setup, errors, official resources, and external ownership boundaries.

05:15.000 --> 05:40.000
The full synthetic workflow is complete. Production migrations and the external backend remain outside the verified claim.
